		<div class="the-comment alt" id="comment-1500651">

		<div class="comment-meta">

			<span class="comment-author">James Mulhern</span>
			<span class="comment-link">
				<a href="#comment-1500651" title="Comment Permalink">
					<span class="comment-date">February 25, 2014</span>
					<span class="comment-middot">&middot;</span>
					<span class="comment-time">7:37 pm</span>
				</a>
			</span>
		</div>
		<div class="comment-content" style="display:block;">

			<p>Great lesson to educate students about current events. I find that most teenagers are not aware of important international conflicts. The background that you provide to the current situation in the Ukraine provides context and history. Helping students get a larger picture in the new globalized word will prepare them for an even more interconnected planet in the future. What happens on the other side of the world has repercussions for all of us. This lesson enables teachers to start the conversation about how what happens in the Ukraine could potentially affect us.  Thank you.</p>
<p>James Mulhern, <a href="//www.synthesizingeducation.net" rel="nofollow">//www.synthesizingeducation.net</a></p>

		</div>
	</div><!-- #comment-## -->
