			<p>I would advise against using David M. Herszenhorn&#8217;s analysis of the &#8216;three core factors&#8217;, largely because he is wrong on two of them, as I explain further here: <a href="//ayellowguard.blogspot.com/2014/02/is-ukrainian-conflict-really-leftover.html" rel="nofollow">//ayellowguard.blogspot.com/2014/02/is-ukrainian-conflict-really-leftover.html</a></p>
<p>It is a very US-centric viewpoint to look at this as any sort of parallel to the Cold War, and to a degree also fails to understand what even the Cold War was really about.</p>

