			<p>The only thing i can comment on this matter is that i respect  the people uniting to help their country.  I am aware that some say they&#8217;re bums who&#8217;ve got nothing better to do or instigators on the government payroll.  But in my opinion there is no actual answer. Some might be bums, some might be payed, but i also know that some of them are there supporting eachother and their cause. People of all ages, all social groups. A sweet, old grandmother might be pouring a molotv cocktail in a nationalists bottle and a manager of a large company might carry ammunition to a student. Of course, everyone has their own individual plan to save Ukraine (some by using violence, others by asking the world for help etc.) and they all have a different vision of the future. .Unfortunately, the Ukranians had bad luck with opposition. The street mob is not controlled by anyone&#8230;One thinig is for certain, and that is that they all came out (the main mass being non-political) to kick Yanukovich and his company&#8217;s ass! RESPECT!</p>

